<subSubSection id="1FD5651DFFD1FFC1FAAFFB7E68A4E5EC" pageId="4" pageNumber="309" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="57703696FFD1FFC1FAAFFB7E68A4E5EC" blockId="4.[1338,2545,724,1502]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="65BBEA84FFD1FFC1FAAFFB7E69D6E4C0" box="[1339,1694,1157,1186]" pageId="4" pageNumber="309">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Golden-white Bare-ear Marmoset is threatened by habitat loss. The Trans-Amazonian Highway cuts through the northern part of its distribution. There is widespread forest loss in the southern part of its known distribution, with areas suffering clear-cutting for industrial agriculture (soy). Recent surveys have increased its known distribution, and a reassessment could change the status of the Golden-white Bare-ear Marmoset to Near Threatened or Least Concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
